post_text: Northern Cass is seeking TWO full time bus drivers starting as soon as possible. The successful candidate would drive a morning and afternoon route. post_text: The Northern Cass Junior High Volleyball season officially kicks off Monday, August 24th. Practice will begin at 4:15 p.m. and end at approximately 5:20 p.m. Be sure you have filled out the Covid Waiver form prior to practice, along with your athlete's physical and HIPAA forms. These forms could have been turned in to the office prior to OR can be turned in at practice tomorrow. We look forward to the season! If you have any questions, please reach out to 7th grade coach Megan Engelke, 8th grade coach Amber Eller, or Athletic Director, John O'Day. Thank you!

post_text:
Good Afternoon Parents/Guardians,

We are currently working on device assignments for the 2020-2021 school year. If your Learner has opted for the Virtual Academy you can disregard this message and I'll be reaching out to you separately.

For those returning to the building you will be assigned a school device. However, some Learners have opted to utilize their own device in the past rather than use the school's device. We are perfectly onboard with that and will work to make sure you have everything you need on your own device. There is one change with that. Beginning this year we are requiring those using their own device to also pay the Technology Fee. The reason behind this is there are many other things in the Tech Departments this helps to pay for, WiFi, apps, software, etc...

If your Learner(s) plans to use a device from home this year will you please send me an email, darin.eller@northerncassschool.com, as soon as you can so we can account for that when assigning devices.

Thank you!
Mr. Eller

post_text: BUS ROUTE INFORMATION: Now that a plan is approved, we can begin the next steps for reopening. A survey will be coming out to all families to collect data, including who will be riding the bus. Your response is needed for successful planning, so please watch your email and respond. That survey will be due Monday, August 10, at 8:00am. After data is compiled and routes can be determined, letters will go out. We anticipate they will be out by the end of next week or early the week of August 17.
text: BUS ROUTE INFORMATION: Now that a plan is approved, we can begin the next steps for reopening. A survey will be coming out to all families to collect data, including who will be riding the bus. Your response is needed for successful planning, so please watch your email and respond. That survey will be due Monday, August 10, at 8:00am. After data is compiled and routes can be determined, letters will go out. We anticipate they will be out by the end of next week or early the week of August 17.

post_text: CAREER OPPORTUNITY: Northern Cass School District is seeking a bus driver for the 2020-21 school year and beyond. Bus drivers are paid $22.70 per hour and are guaranteed four hours per day (a.m. and p.m.). Bus drivers can also drive for activities if they choose and are paid the same rate for driving with a sitting rate of $14.00/hour while watching the event/activity. We can also be flexible with times (only a.m. or p.m.) as we simply need to increase our amount of highly qualified drivers. We will pay for testing and time towards preparing. It has always been a struggle to find drivers at Northern Cass, and we are in need now. If you would consider this opportunity, please contact Dr. Steiner at 701-874-2322 or e-mail Cory.Steiner@northerncassschool.com.

Any questions or concerns can be directed to Paige Carlson by phone call at 701-874-2322.

The special election being held on Tuesday June 23, 2020 is to request an increase to the building fund levy by 5 mills and is being held via mail-in ballot only based on Governor Burgumâ€™s executive order 2020-19.1. BALLOTS MUST BE RETURNED to the School secure drop box by 5:00pm on MONDAY, June 22, or postmarked on June 22.

Absentee ballots will be opened by election officials starting at 2:30 PM on Tuesday, June 23, 2020. This process is open to the public and will be recorded.

The Rural Cass County Emergency Food Pantry will be hosting a mobile food pantry on Thursday, June 11. Food boxes will be available in the parking lot of the following locations from 10-11 A.M. (or when they run out). There will be 20 boxes of assorted meats and 20 boxes of assorted dairy products available at each location.

* Page Elementary School (Page, ND)
* Maple Valley High School (Tower City, ND)
* Northern Cass High School (Rural Hunter, ND)
* Mapleton Elementary School (Mapleton, ND)

Anyone in need of food assistance is welcome. No pre-registration required. Only information collected is the age demographics of the household.

For more information please contact:
Bonnie Oberlander 701-866-7440

The Mobile Food Pantry is made possible by the support of the Great Plains Food Bank.

The NDSU College of Engineering is excited to announce they are creating STEM Kids Take Home kits that families can purchase. There are 9 different kits available in areas like Crime Scene Science, Anatomy, Physics, and Coding. Each kit is $25 and comes with all the required materials and online resources created by their past STEM Kids instructors.

Their online store and more information can be found on the attached link. Orders will be accepted until Friday, June 12th. For Fargo-Moorhead residents, curbside pickup will be available the week of July 10th at the NDSU College of Engineering. For those outside the FM area, we do have grant funding to cover the cost of shipping. Please choose an option at checkout.

If you have any questions, please contact Lauren Singelmann, NDSU Outreach Coordinator | College of Engineering, phone 701-231-5798.

https://www.ndsu.edu/coe/outreach/stem_kids_take_home/

The following was written by Sherise Eagen for an assignment for Mr. Shawn Krinkeâ€™s ELA course. The video accompanies this ELA project.

"My project this time was to try and find my flow. I was able to find my flow while practicing music. I think it went fairly well considering I lost track of time and just kept playing for over an hour with no distractions. It felt nice to be solely focused on one thing and not be worrying about everything I needed to have finished and tests coming up. I was just able to relax. I would do this again for sure, but next time maybe with a different instrument. I really want to learn how to play the ukulele and keyboard. Maybe with enough practice, I could even make my own songs. :)"

* At the lunch buses this week

* At next Monday's homework and material bus delivery

* At the school (bins outside of the south doors)

* Device drop off days (5/20 and 5/21)

For any books not returned by the end of the year (5/21), parents/guardians will be responsible for the cost of the missing books. If you have questions about what your learner has checked out, email Erica.Spangelocarney@northerncassschool.com.

post_text: April was Poetry Month. Mrs. Breiland's seventh grade learners explored figurative language throughout and have used daily journal prompts to practice the techniques to express themselves. At the conclusion of the month, they held a Virtual Poetry Cafe on Zoom. Each learner brought a line or two from their journals to share what they wanted to get across. Each learner had received coffee & hot cocoa packets on the supply routes, so they were able to connect across the distance over coffee and cocoa while sharing their writing.

post_text: One way to make literary connections is to have an interactive experience with the book. In the story, "Because of Winn-Dixie", Gloria Dump hangs empty bottles from a tree in her backyard to represent her past mistakes. She does this to remind herself and others that we can learn from our mistakes and try to do better. If we were at school, Mrs. Margerum would have created this tree in her learning center. With distance learning, her learners sent their bottles to her and she hung them on the tree in her "home learning center."

post_text:
Distance Learning Behind the Scenes:

Each week, our educators compile lessons, activities, and other materials for our learners to use at home. Our office and paraprofessional teams all learned to wear masks and vinyl gloves properly so that they could safely assemble each family's packets and sort them for each bus route. Once those boxes, totes, and assorted supplies are assembled, they are moved to the bus barn where a team of drivers collects them early Monday morning and delivers them (while also picking up completed work) along our normal bus routes. It's a process, but one we are happy to do each week to ensure learning continues even though we cannot be together at this time. #teamwork #SeekSignificance #NCGreatness

Once those boxes, totes, and assorted supplies are assembled, they are moved to the bus barn where a team of drivers collects them early Monday morning and delivers them (while also picking up completed work) along our normal bus routes. It's a process, but one we are happy to do each week to ensure learning continues even though we cannot be together at this time. #teamwork #SeekSignificance #NCGreatness

post_text:
Northern Cass, you are invited to participate in our FIRST EVER Virtual Concert Series! Every learner is welcome to participate in this event. Submit a video (2 minutes or less) showing off their amazing TALENTS! Use the Google Drive Folder link to submit your video. We will review all material before it is shared on our FB page here. Participation is optional, and learners must have parent permission before sharing since it will be posted onto our schoolâ€™s social media.

You may submit under the following categories: Vocal, Instrumental, Movement (Dance), Poetry and/or Visual Arts. For visual arts, please upload a well-lit, clear picture of your artwork. If you are singing, please use the karaoke or instrumental track. For copyright purposes, we cannot share a recording with singing over the original artist.

If you have any questions, please reach out to your fine arts educator. We are very excited for this event and hope it will be a great way to showcase the talent here at Northern Cass!

Please email your video to Miss Vetter, stephanie.vetter@northerncassschool.com.

* Bathrooms will not be available, so please plan accordingly.
